Citation.sTitle: Partial molar volumes of organic solutes in water. XXI: Cyclic ethers at temperatures T = (278 to 373) K and at low pressure
Citation.sAbstract: Density values for dilute aqueous solutions of five cyclic ethers obtained using the Anton Paar DSA 5000  vibrating-tube densimeter and the laboratory-made flow densimeter are presented together with partial  molar volumes at infinite dilution (standard partial molar volumes) calculated from the measured results.  The cyclic ethers were either five-members cycles with one or two oxygen atoms (oxolane, 1,3-dioxolane)  or six-members cycles with one, two, or three oxygen atoms (oxane, 1,4-dioxane, 1,3,5-trioxane).  The measurements were performed at temperatures from T = 278 K up to T = 373 K and at either atmospheric  pressure or at p = 0.5 MPa. The group contribution method is proposed and values of group contributions  are evaluated. Standard partial molar volumes predicted for several other cyclic ethers  including large cycles (crown ethers) are compared with available data from the literature.
